				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Here's the run-once routine I wrote for the NROM Driar port; no NMI intrusion necessary.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">;;; use the power-on wait to detect video system-<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;ldx #0<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;ldy #0<br />@vwait1:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bit $2002<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bpl @vwait1&nbsp; ; at this point, about 27384 cycles have passed<br />@vwait2:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;inx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bne @noincy<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;iny<br />@noincy:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bit $2002<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bpl @vwait2&nbsp; ; at this point, about 57165 cycles have passed<br /><br />;;; BUT because of a hardware oversight, we might have missed a vblank flag.<br />;;;&nbsp; so we need to both check for 1Vbl and 2Vbl<br />;;; NTSC NES: 29780 cycles / 12.005 -&gt; $9B0 or $1361 (Y:X)<br />;;; PAL NES:&nbsp; 33247 cycles / 12.005 -&gt; $AD1 or $15A2<br />;;; Dendy:&nbsp; &nbsp; 35464 cycles / 12.005 -&gt; $B8A or $1714<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp;tya<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;cmp #16<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bcc @nodiv2<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lsr<br />@nodiv2:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;clc<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;adc #&lt;-9<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;cmp #3<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bcc @noclip3<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda #3<br />@noclip3:<br />;;; Right now, A contains 0,1,2,3 for NTSC,PAL,Dendy,Bad<br /></div></div>

					
							<br /><br />
