				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It can be done by <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Detect_TV_system" class="postlink">counting cycles from one NMI to the next</a>. This may mess up on an overclocked NES, so you can either use a <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=22&amp;t=12499" class="postlink">more complicated method to detect overclocked systems</a> or just write off overclocking as undefined behavior.<br /><br />Ninja'd: lidnariq has an interesting way to correct for the $2002 race.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

